This is extremely dangerous! Allowing users to specify arbitrary URLs opens your application to Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF), one of the most critical cloud security vulnerabilities. The Capital One breach in 2019 resulted from exactly this pattern - attackers accessed AWS metadata to steal IAM credentials, exposing 106 million customer records and costing $80+ million in fines.

**VULNERABLE CODE**:

```go
