**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- Attackers can access cloud metadata endpoints (169.254.169.254) to steal IAM/service account credentials
- Internal services, databases, and admin panels become accessible through the vulnerable server
- Network segmentation is completely bypassed - the server acts as a proxy into your infrastructure
- Attackers can pivot to exfiltrate data from internal resources like S3 buckets, databases, or internal APIs

