This is a critical security concern - allowing user-controlled URLs without validation is one of the most dangerous vulnerabilities, known as Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF). The 2019 Capital One breach exposed 106 million records when an attacker exploited SSRF to access AWS metadata and steal IAM credentials.

**VULNERABLE CODE**:

```go
